WLC_EVENT_LOOP_ADD_TIMER(3)                                   WLC API FUNCITONS

NAME

    wlc_event_loop_add_timer - add a timer to the event loop

SYNOPSIS

    struct wlc_event_source* wlc_event_loop_add_timer(int (*cb)(void *arg), 
                                                      void *arg);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_event_loop_add_timer() is used to add a timer to the wlc_event_loop
    that can be triggered after a specific interval which set by using the
    wlc_event_source_timer_update(3) function.

    The callback is only triggered once when the time is met.

    wlc_event_source_remove(3) is used to remove the timer from the
    wlc_event_loop.

RETURN VALUE

    On success wlc_event_loop_add_timer() returns an opaque wlc_event_source
    otherwise it shall return NULL.

NOTES

    The return value of the callback cb is unused.

ALSO SEE

    wlc_event_source_timer_update(3), wlc_event_source_remove(3)
